# OpenBeast weight registry — the supply-chain pin for every shipped GGUF.
#
# Hashes + sizes were computed from the exact files validated on the
# reference box (RTX 5090, 2026-07-17). bootstrap.sh verifies the default
# model against this file after download; scripts/verify-weights.sh checks
# any downloaded weight (size by default, --deep for sha256); doctor runs
# the quick size check. If an upstream HF repo changes a file, verification
# fails loudly — re-pin only after vetting the new file.
#
# Tab-separated: sha256 <TAB> bytes <TAB> local filename <TAB> HF repo <TAB> remote filename ("-" = same as local)
#
# A row may use sha256="PENDING" with bytes=0 when a shipped serve script
# targets a weight not yet downloaded/hashed on the reference box. verify-
# weights.sh treats PENDING as "nothing to verify yet"; replace it with a real
# sha256 + byte size (sha256sum + stat -c%s) once the file is in place.
